review:
A decent space sim/sandbox with RPG elements, its nice, not too in depth overall but could use more complex mechanics and more info in general on what on earth your fleets, civiliian/military are doing, the fleet capacities are a complete joke though when the AI doesnt play by fleet cap/economy rules, but then ,they also dont take over the entire map like in X4 Foundations or Stellaris so its fine, but giant fleet battles instead of tiny fleet groups is nice, the cap on battleships/Dreadnaughts is just mental though when most ai fleets consist of several of these class of ships

TL:DR; 
    Its a good, simple space sim/sandbox with RPG elements but X4 Foundations does a lot more a lot better regarding Sim elements than SPGW

Space simulator. You have ship, open map and its your choose what you do with it. You can be part of epic story or you can create your own even more epic story. 

Pros:
- Graphics and physic - if you like space view you need check this game!!
- Music and sounds - even after 88 hours I am not tired of music, also the effects are very good quality when you use proxima gun you can feel how powerfull its this gun;
- Storyline and custom scenarios;
- Many, many ships, fractions, weapons, items and secrets;
- Very enjoyable shooting and managment of your fleet;
- Super dev team - you can give them suggestions on discord.

Cons:
- Sometimes tracking of crashes working strange.

Note: 10/10 epic journey!

An interesting game and a lot like SW: EaW, but with a slower start. 

Enjoyment - 7/10;
Gameplay - 8/10;
Durability - 6/10;
visuals -7/10 could be better.

I really wanted to like this game, I really did, but there were so many things going on that took away any feelings of joy or satisfaction from this game.  I ended up asking for refund as a result after a few hours of giving it chances to improve but all that ended up happening was a lowering of my expectations and that's not fun.

Navigating the ship around was a choir and rather unintuitive;

Combat felt the same way due to poor camera controls and the fact that enemy ships would continuously whiz past me and the only way I could keep them in a firing arc was to slow my ship down to the point that I was now a sitting duck;

The missions and campaign were supremely boring and I didn’t even bother reading any of the text outlines for them at one point;

Control placement on the middle mouse button are inconvenient as well since the scroll wheel is how you increase/decrease ship speed which ended up getting in the way more often than not;

The UI overall was in the way really.  No readouts on speed beyond a thin bar at the bottom of the screen, poor indications on directional headings, the ship hangar/loadout screens are just an unorganized mess.

Everything about this game feels like this wants to be EVE without actually going to the trouble of putting forth any effort to make that happen.  Definitely a softball pitch that bounces five feet in front of the plate.
